<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06129030 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06129030 </ACCESS><LEADPARA>  Convex Computer Corp. of Richardson, Texas, on Tuesday started a supercomputerslugfest, unveiling three new computer families with one that directlychallenges industry leader Cray Research Inc. The 20 products in the company'sC-3, for third generation, series make supercomputers more accessible bylowering their cost, Convex officials said. Convex's C-3800 family, which willsell from $2.5 million to $8 million, challenges Cray with machines that haveup to eight processors, 4 billion bytes of memory and the ability to make 4billion calculations a second.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Business  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  CONVEX CHALLENGES CRAY RESEARCH  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Financial Digest  </MEMO><BYLINE>  Mercury News Staff and Wire Reports  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910508  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Wednesday  </DAY><MONTH>  May  </MONTH><PG.COL>  3F  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  90  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Wednesday May 8, 199100129030,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>